TY  - JOUR
T1  - Strategy, Control Systems, and Resource Sharing: Effects on Business-Unit Performance
AU  - Govindarajan, V.
AU  - Fisher, Joseph
Y1  - 1990/06/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256325
DO  - 10.5465/256325
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 259
EP  - 285
VL  - 33
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Focusing on business units (SBUs) in diversified firms, this study investigated the relationships among control systems, resource sharing, and competitive strategies and their interactive effects on SBU performance. Empirical results indicate that output control and high resource sharing are associated with higher effectiveness for a low-cost strategy and behavior control and high resource sharing are associated with higher effectiveness for a differentiation strategy.
AB  - Focusing on business units (SBUs) in diversified firms, this study investigated the relationships among control systems, resource sharing, and competitive strategies and their interactive effects on SBU performance. Empirical results indicate that output control and high resource sharing are associated with higher effectiveness for a low-cost strategy and behavior control and high resource sharing are associated with higher effectiveness for a differentiation strategy.
